{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c01f0c30-07c6-4b5b-bf35-23e43fa0dfb3","content":"Here are common web API templates and auth options:\n\n**Templates**\n- **ASP.NET Core Web API** (`dotnet new webapi`) — most popular for C#/.NET\n- **Express.js** (`express-generator`) — Node.js\n- **FastAPI** / **Flask** / **Django REST** — Python\n- **Spring Boot** — Java\n\n**Authentication Options (ASP.NET Core example)**\n| Option | Use Case |\n|---|---|\n| **JWT Bearer** | SPAs, mobile apps, microservices |\n| **OAuth 2.0 / OpenID Connect** | Third-party login (Google, GitHub, etc.) |\n| **Cookie-based (Identity)** | Server-rendered apps |\n| **API Keys** | Simple service-to-service |\n| **Microsoft Identity Platform** | Azure AD / Entra ID |\n\nFor `dotnet new webapi`, you can specify auth with:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual   # Identity + JWT\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg    # Azure AD\ndotnet new webapi --auth None         # No auth (default)\n```\n\nWant me to scaffold a specific project? Let me know your preferred language/framework.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"12318d8c-17e5-443b-a428-0a495fce17b3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - it's a straightforward informational question I can answer from my knowledge.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about common web API templates and authentication options.","outputTokens":353,"requestId":"5023:3BA552:13C2E78:161A4F5:6A066E7C"},"id":"9f6519b1-f0ce-4a6d-b38c-59c1a51a6c82","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:53:28.908Z","parentId":"5d919ecc-5132-4dca-b59f-818d55a6c14e"}
